<rich:panel id="firsttutPage" style="width: 100%;">
	<f:facet name="header">JSFlot ReRender</f:facet>
	After either a click or a drag event has successfully completed, JSFlot has the capability to re-render other components
	on the page. These components are identified by the ID that you give the components in the JSF markup. In the Live 
	Demonstration a h:outputText is re-rendered after a click event with information regarding the data point clicked. 
	The JSF markup to draw both the chart and the output text: 
	<br /><br /><rich:insert id="rerenderinsert" src="/insert/rerender.insert" highlight="xml"></rich:insert>
</rich:panel>

